<page_title>A gas under a piston</page_title>
<text>A gas under a piston

This model shows a gas under pressure. When temperature increases, the gas molecules will move more violently and push the weight on top of it further upwards. Conversely, when the temperature decreases, the gas molecules will move less violently and the weight will move downward. This model is chosen as a gas law demo, not because it is of primary importance but because many people have implemented it one way or another. If you are authoring with Molecular Workbench, you can modify this model and derive your own variations.

 
         

   Related simulation: Density vs. temperature
   Related simulation: NPT-simulation using Andersen barostat
   Related simulation: Another pressure experiment</text>
